item.description:
By default subqueries are executed in the same database as the original query. This behaviour can be changed by appending database name in front of collection name:
{ &#34;$ns&#34; : &#34;databaseName.collectionName&#34;, &#34;$q&#34; : {}, &#34;$p&#34; : {} } This is particularly useful when group_members collection needs to be referenced when working outside of sonargd database:
{ &#34;$ns&#34; : &#34;sonargd.group_members&#34;, &#34;$q&#34; : { &#34;Group Type&#34; : &#34;&lt;Enter Group Type&gt;&#34;, &#34;Group Description&#34; : &#34;&lt;Enter Group Description&gt;&#34; }, &#34;$p&#34; : &#34;Group Member&#34; }
